&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a contract role (6 months) that is covering the Maternity Leave of our Soft Goods Engineering Project Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Engineering Project Managers at Peak Design sit at the center of our New Product Introduction (NPI) process, connecting the product team to the rest of the company and ensuring that information, decisions, and timelines move clearly across every function. Throughout the development cycle, you&#39;ll work hand-in-hand with the product team, owning the cross-functional coordination that keeps launches on track. Beyond NPI, you&#39;ll be an active contributor to the broader product and project management team, taking on initiatives that improve how we run our product lifecycle and how our teams communicate and collaborate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
